dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.resource.res.log.proto.lan.LANProtocol
dataStructure.description:
LAN Protocols operate at the lowest two levels of the OSI model (i.e., physical and data link) and are used to define communications over different types of local area media. The DEN-ng model defines Ethernet, FDDI, and TokenRing as examples of subclasses of this class.
